<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>DownTheBarrel</title>
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, minimum-scale=1, maximum-scale=1" />
        <%# "the Rails method csrf_meta_tag [prevents] cross-site
        request forgery (CSRF), a type of malicious web attack.
        Don’t worry about the details (I don’t);" %>
        <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
        <%# content security policy tag for cross-site scripting %>
        <% csp_meta_tag %>

        <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-bundle.min.css"/>
    </head>

    <body>
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Hello Rails!</h1>
            <p>this will eventually be the header content for the static video cover letter.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="video-cover-letter">
            <%# TODO: figure out play on load (seems like callback territory) %>
            <%= video_tag(['piplup_sidebyside'], :autoplay => "autoplay", :controls => true, :width =>'1420px') %>
        </div>
        <%# slider main container %>
        <swiper-container 
            class="swiperCarousel"
            navigation="true"
            pagination="true"
            pagination-type="progressbar"
            loop="true"
            autoplay="true"
            autoplay-delay="3000"
        >
            <swiper-slide>
                <div class="github-link">
                    <h3>You really did this?</h3>
                    <p>Yeah, I really did. I really did learn ruby to
                            create this site just so I could impress you. </p>
                    <a href="https://github.com/allyhandro/landing-on-rails/tree/main">See for yourself!)</a>
                </div>
            </swiper-slide>
            <swiper-slide>
                <div class="keeping-work-fun">
                    <h3>How I Keep Work Fun</h3>
                    <ul class="funtime-colleague">
                        <li>Just check out some of the classnames on this page!</li>
                        <li>Ever heard of <a href="https://kaomoji.ru/en/">Kaomoji?</a> You will.</li>
                        <li>Documentation? I think you mean ✨documen-slay-tion✨!
                            <%# TODO: replace with the published href link %>
                            <a href="https://www.notion.so/anime-garbage/Project-Down-the-Barrel-6e750f09f58e49eea8ef8770e47cf3c5">
                                Learn, Laugh, and Log with me.
                            </a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <%# TODO  memeliography%>
                            <a>Up to the Minute Pop Culture References</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </swiper-slide>
            <swiper-slide>
                <div class="testimonials">
                    <h3>Testimonials</h3>
                    <div class="quote-carousel">
                        <ul>
                            <li class="affirmations">
                                <p>Your approach to recognizing, communicating,
                                and honouring your needs is nothing short of brilliant.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="affirmations">
                                <p> Something something testimonial </p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </swiper-slide>
        </swiper-container>
        <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-element-bundle.min.js"></script>
        <div class="contact-form">
            <h2>Contact Me</h2>
            <%= render partial: 'contact_form' %>
            <%# TODO: replace with a proper form, maybe something with mailers?" %>
            <%# <textarea placeholder="You're hired."></textarea> %>
        </div>
    </body>
    <footer>
        <p>idk, footer stuff ig.</p>
    </footer>
</html>